{
  "texts": [
    "Beta Shapley Recent work has also questioned the optimality of SV assigning uniform weight to each training subset size [see Eq.",
    "Counterintuitively, Kwon and Zou (2022) show theoretically and empirically that influence estimates on larger training subsets are more affected by training noise than influence estimates on smaller subsets.",
    "As such, rather than assigning all data subset sizes (|D|) uniform weight, Kwon and Zou (2022) argue that smaller training subsets should be prioritized.",
    "Specifically, Kwon and Zou 2022 propose Beta Shapley, which modifies vanilla SV by weighting the training-set sizes according to a positive skew (i.e., left-leaning) beta distribution.",
    "SV has also been applied to study other types of influence beyond training set membership."
  ]
}